DURBAN - Ready… get set… and…. urgh I’ll study later. The run-up to matric exams calls for discipline in the study routines of pupil in order for them to achieve the best results possible. Director and co-founder of Step Up Education, Cindy Glass, described this period as "crunch-time". “But, alas, not all learners feel motivated or willing to put in the effort that is needed at this time. Some learners may, in fact, show little or any interest in studying for their exams, leaving parents and teachers feeling worried about what can be done about it,” she said. Glass has listed tips for parents to help their children avoid procrastination.   SUNDAY TRIBUNE